Cladistic analysis. The data set analyzed under K = 5 to 16 yielded the same tree topology (
Fig. 27
) in each of the concavities (CI = 0.47 , RI = 0.42 ). The tree derived from K = 5 (score = 30.37 ) showed the best character measure support calculated as absolute frequencies, frequency differences and absolute Bremer support. The best relative Bremer support measures were those of K = 7 (score = 29.7 ).

The clade [
A. aris - A. vittigera - A. kuroberobustus
] shares the characters female LR III of 0.63–0.71 , DC 1 of 54– 58 um long, thoracic horn of 524–680 um long, larval AR of 5.30–6.40 , BL 1 / A 2–4 of 0.80–0.88 , A 1 / Ring 0 of 0.70–0.76 and L / W PMx of 2.75–3.30 .

